[[File:GreyshadesRedAirspeeder.jpg|thumb|250px|The airspeeder.]]
This apparently modified '''[[B69 Elektra airspeeder|B69 Elektra]] [[Airspeeder/Legends|airspeeder]]'''<ref name="VivaSpaceVegas">{{SW|url=news/viva-space-vegas-the-history-of-the-marvelous-wheel-part-1|series=Viva Space Vegas! The History of the Marvelous Wheel|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> belonged to [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Simon Greyshade/Legends|Simon Greyshade]] in [[23 BBY/Legends|23 BBY]].<ref name="HonorAndDuty">''[[Star Wars: Republic: Honor and Duty]]''</ref> It matched much of the appearance of his prized [[XJ-6 airspeeder/Legends|XJ-6 airspeeder]]; notable differences between the two included additional seating and a different paint job uncommon to the senator's standard scheme.<ref name="FF29">[[The Official Star Wars Fact File 29|''The Official Star Wars Fact File'' 29]]</ref>

[[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] utilized it to escort the senator to safety.<ref name="HonorAndDuty" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Firsthotrod.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Greyshade's airspeeder as it appears in the comic.]]
While this model is shown on the cover of the comic it appears in, a different [[Airspeeder/Legends|speeder]] is shown in the comic itself. This change may be accidental on the part of the artists, as the speeder was later identified in ''[[Viva Space Vegas! The History of the Marvelous Wheel]]'' to be the speeder shown on the cover. ''Viva Space Vegas! The History of the Marvelous Wheel'' also was the first source to name of Greyshade's vehicle as a B69 Elektra airspeeder.

